---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import DocSection from "../../components/docs/DocSection.astro";
import CommandBlock from "../../components/docs/CommandBlock.astro";
import Callout from "../../components/docs/Callout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="PYRS Docs | Getting Started"
	description="Getting started guide for PYRS runtime usage and first execution flow."
	pageTitle="Getting Started"
>
	<DocSection>
		<p>
			PYRS is a Python interpreter in Rust targeting CPython 3.14 compatibility. This page covers
			the fastest way to install, verify, and run code.
		</p>
	</DocSection>

	<DocSection title="Prerequisites">
		<ul class="m-0 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
			<li>Rust stable toolchain (`rustup`, `cargo`)</li>
			<li>Git</li>
			<li>macOS or Linux</li>
		</ul>
	</DocSection>

	<DocSection title="Install and Verify">
		<p>Install the latest `pyrs` from GitHub and verify your binary is available.</p>
		<CommandBlock
			commands={[
				"cargo install --locked --git https://github.com/BlueBlazin/pyrs --bin pyrs",
				"pyrs --version",
			]}
		/>
		<Callout title="Need more options">
			For all install methods (Cargo source build, Docker, nightly archives), open the{" "}
			<a class="font-medium text-[#b7c8eb] no-underline hover:text-[#d8e1f6]" href="/docs/install/"
				>Installation page</a
			>.
		</Callout>
	</DocSection>

	<DocSection title="Run Python">
		<p>Start with REPL, inline command mode, and source-file execution.</p>
		<CommandBlock
			commands={[
				"pyrs",
				"pyrs -c \"import sys; print(sys.version)\"",
				"pyrs path/to/script.py",
			]}
		/>
	</DocSection>

	<DocSection title="Next Steps">
		<ul class="m-0 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
			<li>
				Review{" "}
				<a class="font-medium text-[#b7c8eb] no-underline hover:text-[#d8e1f6]" href="/docs/reference/"
					>CLI and Environment Reference</a
				>.
			</li>
			<li>Use <code>pyrs --help</code> to inspect runtime options directly from the binary.</li>
			<li>Track release and compatibility progress in the project repository.</li>
		</ul>
	</DocSection>
</DocsLayout>
